'''Bragg's law'''
#{{physics}} equates the [[angle]] <math>(\theta)</math> between the [[incident]] and [[scattered]] [[ray]] to the [[spacing]] <math>(d)</math> between the [[crystal]] [[plane]]s and the [[wavelength]] <math>(\lambda)</math> of the [[radiation]] - <math>n\lambda=2d\sin(\theta) \,</math>

